		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Thu, Aug 17th 9:26 PM 2000 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=10&mid=96656199227915&post=1&replyto=96656199227915"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>   <a name=96656199227915></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=466"><span id=>Niccodemus</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br>5 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.50]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>It's important to note however that you will only gain weapon skill increases while fighting monsters that con blue or higher, and (It's my understanding) that only with primary <br>weapon used while dual wielding. I've tried using multiple weapon skills with other CHARs<br> and found that the skills themselves wind up taking way too long to max for a LvL, <br>especially when trying to train in either of the 2 handers. My LvL was increasing much faster<br>than my weapon skill at lower Lvls and I was left without any solid attack power.&nbsp;&nbsp;As a <br>dual wielding class I would suggest picking 2 of the one handed wepon skills (yes, piercing counts, even when using 2 spears) Work them both up gradually and when you finally get<br>dual wield switch the weapon in your primary hand. This will still give you plenty of weapon choices and if you come across a good 1HB after training in 1HS and piercing, you have<br>twice as many weapon options to get in trade for it. And as a note to rangers ALWAYS USE A <br>BOW TO PULL!!!! Archery will inevitably be the slowest weapon skill to raise as you never <br>fire as many arrows as you will use any other weapon in a fight (even given the root spells<br>available to us). So use those arrows up, with the critical hits we get, the double DMG<br>against non-rooted/non-moving targets, and the quality of the ranger only bows (some of<br>the best DMG/DLY ratios in the game) it is the one weapon skill you will come to appreciate<br>more as your level goes up.   </p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>ranger- Cazic Thule<br>Peace be the journey.</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >4 Replies</td></tr></table><