		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></a><b><span id=></span></b>
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Well, to put it bluntly... what a crock. You obviously just didn't wait long enugh to start cross-training your weapon skills. When you first start out concentrate mainly on 1HS as you are gonna need your shield to stay alive in CB and BB. But, don't neglect 2HS either at low levels, cause you WILL regret it later. Now as to the others, once dual-wield is achieved, go for either a 1HB or piercing (whichever suits your fancy) in your off-hand, so you can still raise the skill level in your group & produce some decent damage for it. HPH works really well as those orcs are just sitting targets for ya. Then, switch out and put the piercer or blunt in your primary hand for even bigger boosts of skill increases. This will allow you to keep your 1HS and 2HS maxxed out, while building other skills, because it will take a while to level at 17 and afterwards, enough to keep ya maxxed on everything. As for 2HB.... well, that is just gonna take a group of friends or guildmates to help ya out with. Ask for help in the fact you get to hit with it and not die by them actually keeping you in group as a 6th wheel and healing ya. This really doesn't take that long though and you'll be swinging pretty decently in no time. Just go for the shovel in Rathe that has that killer lower delay or one of the new ones from Kunark to help. <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;  Anyways, the only problem I foresee is that you neglect any one of these skills for a long time and it falls behind. Barring that, you should be able to be a master of arms with relatively no problems or hinderances to grouping very quickly and efficiently... Ranger-style! 8 )<br><br>Raskle Bryarpatch<br>Level 30 Wood Elf Ranger<br>Guildmaster of Black Diamond<br>Bristlebane Server</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 